Every police force in England and Wales will be required to record anti-Muslim hate crimes and treat them as seriously as anti-Semitic attacks if the Tories win the next General Election .
In a move hailed by Islamic groups , Mrs May said that police will have to record Islamophobic attacks as a separate category , just as anti antiSemitic crimes are recorded separately .
At present some forces , including London 's Metropolitan Police , do record them as hate crimes .
Charities say there has been a steady rise of Islamophobic hate crimes in Britain .